1. From Graphs to Fields: Knowledge as a Dynamic Field

So far we treated ideas as a graph:

concepts → nodes
relationships → edges

But many modern systems treat networks as continuous fields.

Instead of discrete connections, we define a knowledge density function over concept space.

Mathematically this looks like a diffusion system:

\frac{\partial \phi}{\partial t} = D\nabla^2\phi + S(x,t)

Interpretation:
	•	\phi = knowledge intensity
	•	D = diffusion constant
	•	S(x,t) = sources of new information

So ideas propagate like energy through a field.

